# hephaestus-automation-loop-branch-sync-drive-green - History

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-29)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus PR #1633 / issue #1405 drive-green recovery.
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added the PR #1633 failure mode where a CI-fix session advanced HEAD but left tracked residual changes dirty, making the PR unsafe or impossible to push.
- Added the sessionless existing-PR conflict recovery rule: direct agents may start a fresh implementation session when there is no saved implementer session id.
- Added residual commit rules for tracked-path allowlists, refusing unmerged status codes, staging deleted tracked files with `git add -u`, and avoiding broad residual staging.
- Added the strict-mypy implementation trap: explicit calls are required instead of dynamic `**kwargs` when forwarding optional `allowed_paths`.
- Added PR #1633 / issue #1405 to Results & Parameters and Verified On.

### Why
ProjectHephaestus PR #1633 was not blocked only by the original C901 refactor. The drive-green
path exposed automation reliability bugs: conflicted existing PRs could dead-end without a saved
session, CI-fix agent turns could leave residual tracked work uncommitted after making a commit,
and the typed commit-helper wrapper needed a mypy-visible branch for `allowed_paths`. Capturing
these under the existing automation-loop drive-green skill keeps the learning with the workflow
that operators will search when a PR appears fixed locally but cannot be pushed or merged.

